<div id="categories-page">
    <h1>Categories</h1>
    <ul id="categories-list">
        <li class="category">
            <h2 class="category-title">Soft</h2>
            <p class="category-description">A soft cheese is a cheese that has a high moisture content and a soft texture. Examples include Brie and Camembert.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="category">
            <h2 class="category-title">Hard</h2>
            <p class="category-description">A hard cheese is a cheese that has a low moisture content and a firm texture. Examples include Cheddar and Parmesan.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="category">
            <h2 class="category-title">Blue</h2>
            <p class="category-description">Blue cheese is a type of cheese that has been inoculated with mold cultures, giving it a distinct blue or green marbling. Examples include Roquefort and Gorgonzola.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="category">
            <h2 class="category-title">Processed</h2>
            <p class="category-description">Processed cheese is a cheese product made from a blend of natural cheeses and other ingredients, often used for its melting properties. Examples include American cheese and cheese spreads.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="category">
            <h2 class="category-title">Fresh</h2>
            <p class="category-description">Fresh cheese is a cheese that has not been aged or matured. It has a mild flavor and a creamy texture. Examples include Ricotta and Mascarpone.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="category">
            <h2 class="category-title">Semi-Soft</h2>
            <p class="category-description">Semi-Soft cheese is a cheese that has a smooth and creamy texture, but is firmer than fresh cheese. Examples include Havarti and Munster.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="category">
            <h2 class="category-title">Semi-Hard</h2>
            <p class="category-description">Semi-Hard cheese is a cheese that has a firmer texture than semi-soft cheese, but is not as hard as aged cheese. Examples include Gouda and Edam.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="category">
            <h2 class="category-title">Soft-Ripened</h2>
            <p class="category-description">Soft-Ripened cheese is a cheese that has been aged for a short period of time, resulting in a soft and creamy texture. Examples include Brie and Camembert.</p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>